<subSubSection id="FC212F2221CDDF3D4EB2F8C2EE447891" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="9B3B8E27AC1E37783AE92C3041C055E6" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Schotenkresse, Schmalwand</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="2125623676E0613096B92A12DF8789A7" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" type="description">
<paragraph id="574200C4D5E666E7E642A42696DA292C" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">
Unterscheidet sich von der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="695DEE9D7CC0168119EAAD47EB169C8C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB79C99C209B61873706A39EC641D0D1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Arabis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(S. 226) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="F6689734750F1D5D4819D4EB6C899F13" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">
<normalizedToken id="8C958DEB7C438B5A42B4F32376E51D76" originalValue="Kelchblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Kelchblaetter</normalizedToken>
weniger als 2 mm lang;
</emphasis>
innere 
<normalizedToken id="FBAD5222F8305CF4884335F2841C5F81" originalValue="Kelchblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Kelchblaetter</normalizedToken>
am Grunde nur wenig ausgebuchtet; Fruchtstiele ⅓-⅔ so lang wie die 
<normalizedToken id="3B0E88D207FB7C76464A53CE20D7C33D" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="1A2A9521A197BEE741E453AF20994901" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">
<normalizedToken id="CD444FEFA537C81C898E96A642B39BFF" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
nicht abgeflacht, im Querschnitt abgerundet 4kantig.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A348AB3BD38D6311F7B5EDA878B61D5" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="E21939641A94DDBFEE1287A10BDE1FC5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="782B313063005C9F3F4418CB98C58458" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Arabidopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="D103843AD3418D1A7EE4DD4B58A22C85" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">umfasst</normalizedToken>
etwa 
<emphasis id="3925A4BDAD6A2FBE47282BD14A4B0BB5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">12 vorwiegend mediterrane und westasiatische Arten</emphasis>
. Die Begrenzung der Gattung namentlich 
<normalizedToken id="2C8CA42987FCF64A95FC9E0F1D107620" originalValue="gegenüber" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">gegenueber</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="3C8B152CF826B65C90DE89AB19786D70" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">
<taxonomicName id="2C4C51C45E9EEEE56C53AC259BC037A8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardaminopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Cardaminopsis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DFAC28B453CDD77EE341A12B6E9078AA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Arabis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
und 
<taxonomicName id="C353400E4D43251F29B469260563FEEA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Sisymbrium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="883DCC9C9BB6EBE96DDC7BF92F943429" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Sisymbrium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ist sehr unklar. Mit der 
<normalizedToken id="680A986BCDFF89EAC945A2405E22AB38" originalValue="nordwesteuropäischen" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">nordwesteuropaeischen</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="AAD8B4BADAD25321FBA7157DFF75942B" authority="(Fr.) Norrl." authorityName="Norrl." baseAuthorityName="Fr." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suecica">
<emphasis id="D2829DFE302BCB1D67BA3611C5DFF87C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">A. suecica</emphasis>
(Fr.) Norrl.
</taxonomicName>
konnten erfolgreich Kreuzungen sowohl mit 
<taxonomicName id="A2690AE4ECA694F891F97BE6E69380F8" authority="(L.) Heynh." authorityName="Heynh." baseAuthorityName="L." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thaliana">
<emphasis id="3642195F1445E6A1D0422525803C2F8A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">A. Thaliana</emphasis>
(
<authorityName id="7D890F3C87533898F0B08C616195E733" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">L.</authorityName>
) Heynh.
</taxonomicName>
wie mit 
<taxonomicName id="BC7D6DC3DF641FA25D2CFE17597FD4BC" authority="(L.) Hayek" authorityName="Hayek" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardaminopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis id="26DCAA651BB2BA15A88A5B661396CAFD" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Cardaminopsis arenosa</emphasis>
(
<authorityName id="43C2787C333FDEBF8135D65845426DC9" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">L.</authorityName>
) Hayek
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="8D533298388A4786BCB39A3598A396CC" originalValue="durchgeführt" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">durchgefuehrt</normalizedToken>
werden (Laibach 1958). Die Gattung ist deshalb 
<normalizedToken id="AA219BE6B7C746468E94409C5402B7EE" originalValue="nächstverwandt" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">naechstverwandt</normalizedToken>
mit 
<taxonomicName id="B16FE4A25DD12E9804888A72358B1F13" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardaminopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="26C296B1C35B836B90B6F1E05C79E748" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Cardaminopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, auch wenn die Samen bei 
<taxonomicName id="BC6DD1BF6D0B23B3C28E50E1620813A6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="77F10892AE8A258B4DAE0626F5CDC888" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Arabidopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="8671436123B3CB95259AB84F6A3CD7E4" originalValue="rückenwurzelig" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">rueckenwurzelig</normalizedToken>
und bei 
<taxonomicName id="EA99C55DE069046CC45815C29F98DDD4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardaminopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="309AD5D34CC1307CA932B596A47CFAA7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Cardaminopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seitenwurzelig sind (vgl. hiezu auch Janchen 1964a). 
<normalizedToken id="803C5777E0827E8ABC338C5C34BFD002" originalValue="Měsíček" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Mesicek</normalizedToken>
(1967) erhielt Bastarde zwischen 
<taxonomicName id="B813CACA963B0BCE8A1E3DCBF873C6F6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thaliana">
<emphasis id="B85B52B8FB51185E3BEEF2880620CD06" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">A. Thaliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und diploiden Pflanzen der 
<normalizedToken id="A71354CE37E30D47C42E3F8FB49CA67D" originalValue="osteuropäischen" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">osteuropaeischen</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="C24C58AB4659C5ADFBA61B0A3A10ACAB" authority="(L.) Hiit." authorityName="Hiit." baseAuthorityName="L." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardaminopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petraea">
<emphasis id="48D1DC90D7F588A94E35D082EF0A4EC5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">Cardaminopsis petraea</emphasis>
(
<authorityName id="1C8EEF3010CD65E027DA64C04DB4F494" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">L.</authorityName>
) Hiit.
</taxonomicName>
(dagegen keine mit tetraploiden Pflanzen von 
<taxonomicName id="056F81205AF432F48937DFD9EE89F233" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardaminopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis id="E68B8A8A0DC83C580A188224D5271477" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="226">C. arenosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
